1.31, n 1
&lt;U+76CA&gt;&lt;U+90E8&gt;&lt;U+8006&gt;&lt;U+820A&gt;&lt;U+50B3&gt;
Yi Bu Qijiu Zhuan
Biographies of the Seniors of the Yi Region
At its first reference, Pei Songzhi explicitly attributes Yi Bu Qijiu Zhuan to Chen Shou. However, he later attributes both an Yi Bu Qijiu Zhuan and Yi Bu Qijiu Zhi (&lt;U+5FD7&gt;) to one Chen Shu (&lt;U+9673&gt;&lt;U+8853&gt;). See Records of the Three Kingdoms, 42.1027, biography of Li Zhuan (&lt;U+674E&gt;&lt;U+8B54&gt;). According to the biography of Chen Shou in the Chronicles of Huayang, Chen Shu was a contributor to a Ba&lt;U+2013&gt;Shu Qijiu Zhuan, which prompted Chen Shou to compile Yi Bu Qijiu Zhuan. It is also attributed to Chen Shou in the Book of Jin. The Book of Sui attributes Yi Bu Qijiu Zhuan to a Chen Changshou (&lt;U+9673&gt;&lt;U+9577&gt;&lt;U+58FD&gt;). See Gao Min (2007), p 14.
Yizhou Qijiu Zhuan, cited by Pei Songzhi only once, may be identified with Yi Bu Qijiu Zhuan.
Contains biographies of people from Yi Province
