52.1219&lt;U+2013&gt;1220; biography of Zhang Zhao
Classics
Quoting classics was an inescapable reality of Chinese political and academic life as early as the Eastern Zhou period.34 Pei Songzhi often cites classics in order to contextualize quotations made by speakers in Chen Shou's original text,35 and occasionally to explain the philosophy or background behind a person's actions.36 These works do not constitute historical sources for Pei Songzhi's purposes, but are included here for sake of completeness.
